value.value: A shoot meristematic apical cell that is part of a gametophore.

definition.value: Occurs in the non-vascular shoot system of the gametophyte of mosses and leafy liverworts.

value.value: A shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is part of a gametophore (PO:0030018).

definition.value: Found in mosses and leafy liverworts. A stem or branch of the leafy part of a bryophyte.

value.value: A branch that is part of a gametophore.

definition.value: A branch of the leafy part of a bryophyte shoot system.

value.value: A stem that is part of a gametophore.

definition.value: A stem (the primary axis) of the leafy part of a bryophyte shoot system.

value.value: A shoot axis meristematic apical cell at the tip of a gametophore axis.

definition.value: Occurs at the tips of the stems and branches of bryophytes.

label.value: vascular shoot axis meristematic apical cell

value.value: A shoot axis meristematic apical cell at the tip of a shoot apex in a shoot system that has as part vascular tissue.

definition.value: Occurs in some ferns in their sporophytic phase.

value.value: A gametophyte apical cell that is part of a thallus.
A vegetative bud that develops into a gametophore.

definition.value: Occurs in mosses and leafy liverworts. Develops from a caulonema cell in mosses.

value.value: A whole plant in the gametophytic phase that has a flat growth form and no distinct organs.

definition.value: A thallus is a gametophyte of liverworts and pteridophytes and develops from a short-lived protonema. Roughly two dimensional growth results from division of a single apical cell. Thalli may be ribbon or heart shaped or almost filamentous. Although there are no distinct organs, there may be tissue differentiation and dichotomous branching.

value.value: A bract (PO:0009055) that subtends an antheridium (PO:0025125).

definition.value: When an antheridium occurs on a specialized lateral branch of the gametophore, all of the phyllomes on that branch are usually perigonial bracts. If an antheridium occurs on a main axis of the gametophore, usually only the terminal phyllomes are perigonial bracts.

value.value: A plant organ that is the base of a whole plant in the sporophytic phase and attaches it to the gametophore.

definition.value: Found in bryophytes and some pteridophytes. In mosses, the foot is located below the seta. In ferns, the foot is formed from the upper hypobasal quandrant of the embryo. The sporophyte foot serves for both attachment and absorption. The outer portion of the foot is composed of absorptive transfer cells.

value.value: A bract (PO:0009055) that subtends an archegonium (PO:0025126).

definition.value: When an archegonium occurs on a specialized lateral branch of the gametophore, all of the phyllomes on that branch are usually perichaetal bracts. If an archegonium occurs on a main axis of the gametophore, only the terminal phyllomes are usually perichaetal bracts. The two or three terminal-most perichaetal bracts may fuse to form a gametophytic perianth.

value.value: A collective phyllome structure that consists of two or more of the most distal perichaetal bracts on a gametophore axis and surround a capsule.

definition.value: The perichaetal bracts may fuse laterally in the gametophytic perianth. The gametophytic perianth is not the same structure as a perianth (PO:0009058) in angiosperms.

value.value: A stalk (PO:0025066) that supports a spore capsule, the sporangium (PO:0025094).

definition.value: Found in some bryophytes, especially mosses and liverworts.

value.value: A stalk (PO:0025066) that supports an antheridium head (PO:0030075).

definition.value: Found in mosses and other bryophytes such as the liverwort Marchantiales.

value.value: A stalk (PO:0025066) that supports an archegonium head (PO:0030034).

definition.value: Found in Marchantiales.

value.value: A stalk (PO:0025066) that is the basal part of an antheridium (PO:0025125).

definition.value: The antheridium stalk raises the antheridium (PO:0025125) from the antheridium head (PO:0030075).

value.value: A stalk (PO:0025066) that the basal part of an archegonium (PO:0025126).

definition.value: Raises the venter above the rest of the gametophyte.

value.value: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that develops from an archegonium (PO:0025126) and is a cap or hood enclosing the sporangium (syn: spore capsule; PO:0025094).

definition.value: Found in bryophytes. The spore capsule calyptra is a membranous or hairy cap or hood, composed of gametophytic tissue (venter; PO:0030038) that protects the embryonic sporophyte within the archegonium (PO:0025126). In some species, it may persist after the sporophyte develops and gets carried upward as the seta (PO:0030032) elongates. The spore capsule calyptra is usually lost before the spores are released, and its shape can be used for identification purposes.

value.value: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is the enlarged basal part of an archegonium (PO:0025126) and has an archegonium egg cell (PO:0025122) located in it.

definition.value: After fertilization, the venter develops into the spore capsule calyptra (PO:0030037), which protects the sporangium (syn: spore capsule; PO:0025094) containing the developing sporophyte.

value.value: A cardinal organ part (PO:0025001) that is the elongated, apical part of an archegonium (PO:0025126).

definition.value: Early in development, the archegonium neck is occluded by a single row of neck canal cells (PO:0030065). At maturity, the neck canal cells (PO:0030065) and the ventral canal cell (PO:0025524) disintegrate, creating a archegonium neck canal (PO:0030066) for the plant sperm cells (PO:0000084) to enter the archegonium (PO:0025126).

value.value: A cardinal organ part that is the basal (distal) part of a sporangium.

definition.value: Term used for bryophytes and pteridophytes. The sporangium base is the sterile part of the sporangium below the sporangium theca. If swollen and distinct from the rest of the sporangium, it is called an apophysis or hypophysis.

value.value: A cardinal organ part that is the main body of a sporangium and has spores located in it.

definition.value: Term used for bryophytes and pteridophytes.

value.value: A single or double circle of peristome teeth inside a sporangium mouth.

definition.value: The peristome is located under the operculum, if an operculum is present. Upon maturity of a capsule, the teeth of the peristome open to release the spores.

value.value: A cardinal organ part that is a single lobe of a peristome.

definition.value: Generally triangular. Peristome teeth may be simple or compound, and may be attached by their tips to the epiphragm.

value.value: A cardinal organ part that is the apical part of a spore capsule that separates from the rest of the capsule during dehiscence.

definition.value: Found in mosses. May remain partly attached to the rest of the capsule.

value.value: A ground tissue cell with thickened cell walls.

definition.value: Found only in bryophytes in gametophore axes, setae, or leaves. Functions in support rather than conduction. May or may not retain a living protoplast at maturity.

value.value: A gametophyte meristematic apical cell that is part of a protonema.
A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that has as parts hydroid (PO:0025032) cells and cells of no other types.

definition.value: A hydrome is composed of only hydroids. Found in bryophytes, in the center of a non-vascular shoot axis (PO:0025029) such as a gametophore (PO:0030018) or seta (PO:0030032). Often surrounded by the leptome (PO:0030048). May function in water conduction and may provide support.

value.value: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that has as parts leptoid (PO:0025033) cells and cells of no other types.

definition.value: A leptome is composed of only leptoids (PO:0025033). Found in bryophytes, in non-vascular shoot axes such as a gametophore axis or seta (PO:0030032) or in the midrib of a non-vascular leaf. Often surrounding a central hydrome. May function in the conduction of organic substances, similar to phloem in vascular plants.

value.value: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059) that is the sub-epidermal layer of a sporangium wall (PO:0025306).

definition.value: Term used for vascular plants to describe the outermost layer of a sporangium wall that is internal to the exothecium.

value.value: A portion of ground tissue (PO:0025059)  that has as parts stereid cells (PO:0030045) and no other cell types.

definition.value: A stereome is composed of only stereids. Found only in bryophytes in gametophore axes or non-vascular leaves. May function in support.

value.value: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is an axial strand in the center of a gametophore axis (PO:0030020) or seta (PO:0030032) and has as part a hydrome (PO:0030047) or a leptome (PO:0030048).

definition.value: Often contains both hydrome and leptome. Found in bryophytes. The term central strand is sometimes used to describe a protostele in vascular plants, but this ontology class should only be used for non-vascular plants. Analogous to a vein or vascular bundle in vascular plants.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of an antheridium jacket layer (PO:0030053).
A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is a single layer of cells on the outside of an antheridium (PO:0025125).

definition.value: Cells in the antheridium jacket layer surround the spermatogenous cells (PO:0025525) and do not give rise to antheridium sperm cells (PO:0025120).

value.value: A portion of parenchyma tissue that forms a circular membrane extending from a spore capsule columella and attached to the ends of the peristome teeth that covers a spore capsule mouth.

definition.value: Present in some moss species of the family Polytrichaceae.

value.value: A gametophore axis that is a leafless extension of a gametophore stem or branch on which a sporophyte is borne.

definition.value: Raises the sporophyte above the perichaetial bracts. Found in Sphagnum and Andreaea.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that divides to gives rise to a sporocyte (PO:0006204) and is part of a sporangium (PO:0025094).

definition.value: May also give rise to sterile cells such as elators (in liverworts) or tapetal cells. In most species outside seed plants, multiple archesporial cells are part of an archesporium or sporogenous tissue.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) located at the base of a non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075) adjacent to where the leaf attaches to the stem (PO:0009047).

definition.value: Found in mosses. Alar cells occur in an area at the base of a leaf that may be triangular, ovate or rectangular and is sometimes called the alar region. They are different in size, shape, color, thickness, or ornamentation from other cells in the leaf.

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that develops from a cell in a protonema (PO:0030003) and has a thick cell wall.

definition.value: Found in mosses. A brachycyte is a drought tolerant cell that can act as a gemma (PO:0025614) and may give rise to a new plant. Cells of a protonema (PO:0030003) may develop into brachycytes under stress. May form a chain or be separated by tmema cells (PO:0030059).

value.value: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) at the base of a gemma (PO:0025614) or adjacent to a brachycyte (PO:0030058) that breaks down to allow abscission of the gemma or brachycyte.

definition.value: May be a single cell adjacent to a brachycyte (PO:0030058) or part of a portion of tmema tissue.

value.value: An axillary hair that grows in a leaf axil of a non-vascular leaf.

definition.value: Found in pleurocarpous mosses. Form in the axils of leaf primordia and may disappear when the gametophore is mature.

value.value: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that has as parts tmema cells (PO:0030059).

definition.value: Found in bryophytes at the base of a gemma (PO:0025614). Participates in abscission of the gemma.

value.value: An axillary hair terminal cell that is the long terminal cell of a gametophore axillary hair.
A axillary hair base that is the basal part of a gametophore axillary hair, below the gametophore axillary hair terminal cell.

definition.value: Consists of two to a dozen cells.

value.value: An axillary hair basal cell that is part of a gametophore axillary hair base.
A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is one of the axial row of cells in an immature archegonium neck (PO:0030039).

definition.value: During archegonium development, the archegonium neck canal cells (PO:0030065) and the ventral canal cell (PO:0025524) disintegrate, creating a archegonium neck canal for the plant sperm cells (PO:0000084) to enter the archegonium (PO:0025126).

value.value: A canal (PO:0025132) in the center of an archegonium neck (PO:0030039).

definition.value: During archegonium development, the archegonium neck canal cells (PO:0030065) and the ventral canal cell (PO:0025524) disintegrate, creating a archegonium neck canal for the plant sperm cells (PO:0000084) to enter the archegonium (PO:0025126).

value.value: An protonema sub-apical initial that gives rise to a branch of a protonema.

definition.value: May give rise to a chloronema, caulonema, protonema rhizoid, tmema cell, or brachycyte.

value.value: A plant epidermal initial cell (PO:0000349) that gives rise to an epidermal rhizoid (PO:0030071).

definition.value: Part of the epidermis of a thallus or gametophore of a bryophyte or pteridophyte in the gametophytic phase or the stem of a monocot in the sporophytic phase.
